test-industry-keyword.title: Johnson backs Virginia wind project in break with Trump
test-industry-keyword.snippet: House Speaker Mike Johnson is supporting an offshore wind project in Virginia, despite the Trump administration halting similar projects.

test-industry-keyword.title: Scientists Just Built a Detector That Could Finally Catch Dark Matter
test-industry-keyword.snippet: Physicists have developed a new superconducting detector sensitive enough to detect dark matter particles smaller than electrons.

expanded-industry-term.title: US Manufacturing Expands at Fastest Pace Since 2022 on Demand
expanded-industry-term.snippet: US manufacturing is expanding at the fastest rate in more than three years on stronger demand that's also fueling sustained inflationary pressures.  The S&P Global flash August factory purchasing managers index rose 3.5 points to 53.3, the highest since May 2022.

expanded-industry-term.title: New U.S. Manufacturing Operations Announced in August 2025
expanded-industry-term.snippet: In August 2025, America's manufacturing base continued to expand across a wide range of sectors. Biotech companies announced cutting-edge pharmaceutical and medical isotope plants, heavy industry invested in energy infrastructure and materials production, and consumer goods makers expanded footprints to meet demand.

test-company-keyword.title: Graphene Just Broke a Fundamental Law of Physics
test-company-keyword.snippet: For the first time, scientists have observed electrons in graphene behaving like a nearly perfect quantum fluid, challenging a long-standing puzzle in physics.

test-company-keyword.title: Scientists Just Built a Detector That Could Finally Catch Dark Matter
test-company-keyword.snippet: Physicists have unveiled a new superconducting detector sensitive enough to hunt dark matter particles smaller than electrons. By capturing faint photon signals, the device pushes the search into uncharted territory.

expanded-company-term.title: Salesforce inks major New York office expansion to mirror growth across AI business
expanded-company-term.snippet: Salesforce is expanding its New York City office by 25%, adding over 71,000 square feet to accommodate growth driven by the artificial intelligence boom.  The expansion signifies the company's commitment to the New York market and its focus on creating spaces that support collaboration between humans and AI agents.

expanded-company-term.title: Quantum Base wins PS250,000 contract expansion for Q-ID tech
expanded-company-term.snippet: Quantum Base Holdings PLC secured a £250,000 expansion to an existing contract with its largest customer, an international security printer.  The expansion involves the company's Q-ID authentication technology, adding features and supporting a wider range of smartphone models. This represents a significant step in the commercial rollout of Q-ID technology.

test-regulatory-keyword.title: FDA Faces Blowback Over Stricter Regulation of Lab-Developed Tests
test-regulatory-keyword.snippet: The US Food and Drug Administration (FDA) is facing pushback over its plans to more strictly regulate lab-developed tests.  The new rule will treat facilities developing and using lab tests as manufacturers, requiring FDA review and new quality standards.

test-regulatory-keyword.title: MedPage Today - FDA Gets Pushback on Move to Regulate Lab Developed Tests
test-regulatory-keyword.snippet: Patient advocates, clinicians, and others debated the level of regulation needed for lab-developed diagnostic tests, questioning the extent to which the FDA's oversight should mirror that of pharmaceutical drugs.

expanded-regulatory-term.title: Council to vote on stricter licensing, platform rules for short-term rentals
expanded-regulatory-term.snippet: The proposed ordinance would impose new licensing and eligibility standards, add enforcement mechanisms and expand regulatory obligations for platforms like Airbnb and VRBO.

expanded-regulatory-term.title: Financial Services: Regulatory Recap week commencing 8 September 2025
expanded-regulatory-term.snippet: This Bill expands regulatory perimeter of the Payment Systems (Regulation) Act 1998 (Cth) to include new and emerging payment systems and participants within the payments regulatory framework.
